race.comment: BRADBURY'S MOMENT (9) showed enough in his debut campaign when bumping into a couple of smart ones as a juvenile. His recent trial was good at this track and Brad Parnham hops in the saddle fresh. May need a touch of luck from the draw, but is good enough to shed his maiden tag. GODLESS STORM (2) hits this third-up and drops back to 1000m today. That's some query, though a big field and solid tempo looks on the cards. Has the race fitness and upside and can make his presence felt. LET'S GO JARPO (4) is a 6YO on debut but his only trial coming in was very sharp. Can be in the finish. ALEBRIJE (15) is another on debut who has shown plenty at the trials and is not to be discounted.
